HEADWORD: Dowagerism
<hw>Dow"a*ger*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The rank or
condition of a dowager; formality, as that of a dowager. Also used
figuratively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Mansions that have passed away into <qex>dowagerism</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Thackeray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dowcet</ent>⟦br⟧
